value.value: A circulating gamma-delta T cell that is CD27-positive and capable of producing IFN-gamma.
A circulating gamma-delta T cell that expresses RORgamma(t), is CD27-negative and is capable of IL-17 secretion.

label.value: CD25-positive, CD27-positive immature gamma-delta T cell

value.value: A CD25-positive, CD27-positive immature gamma-delta T cell found in the thymus that has an immature phenotype (i.e. CD24-high, CD25-high, CD62L-high, CD44-high, CD2-low, CD5-low).
A T cell with a receptor of limited diversity that is capable of immediate effector functions upon stimulation.
A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, CCR5-high, CD45RA-negative, and capable of producing IL-17 and some IFNg.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'Tc17 CD8+ T cell', but its logical definition includes additional known characteristics of Tc17 T cells.  Found in the CD27-positive, CD28-positive or CD27-negative, CD28-positive fractions with the phenotype CCR4-negative and CCR7-negative (this sentence not part of definition).

value.value: Regular cardiac myocyte of a cardiac atrium.
A cardiac myocyte of the interatrial region of the heart.
Regular cardiac myocyte of a cardiac ventricle.
A stomal cell of the ovary
A stromal cell of the ovarian cortex.
A stromal cell of the ovarian medulla.
Epidermal cells that do not contain keratin. Cell type is usually associated with moist epidermal tissues.

label.value: type II cell of adrenal cortex
Type II cell of adrenal cortex

value.value: A cell in the zona fasciculata that produce glucocorticoids, e.g cortisol.

label.value: type III cell of adrenal cortex
Type III cell of adrenal cortex

value.value: A cell in the zona reticularis that produce sex hormones.

A endothelial cell of a lymphatic vessel. The border of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell of initial lymphatics are joined by specialized buttons. The discontinuous feature of buttons distinguishes them from zippers in collecting lymphatics, but both types of junctions are composed of proteins typical of adherens junctions and tight junctions found in the endothelium of blood vessels. Buttons seal the sides of flaps of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell, leaving open the tips of flaps as routes for fluid entry without disassembly and reformation of intercellular junctions.

label.value: Cuboidal endothelial cell of vascular tree

value.value: An endothelial cell of the vascular tree, which includes blood vessels and lymphatic vessels.

definition.value: These cells are reportedly CD31-positive, CD34-positive, CD144-positive, TAL1-positive.

value.value: A sebum secreting cell of the skin that secretes sebum into the hair follicles.

label.value: active chief cell of parathyroid gland

value.value: A parathyroid chief cell that is actively secreting hormone. Have large Golgi complexes with numerous vesicles and small membrane-bound granules; secretory granules are rare, cytoplasmic glycogen sparse, much of the cytoplasm being occupied by flat sacs of granular endoplasmic reticulum in parallel arrays; in normal humans, inactive chief cells outnumber active chief cells in a ratio of 3-5:1

label.value: dark cell of eccrine sweat gland

value.value: A cell pyramidal in shape, with their broad ends facing and forming the greater extent of the lining of the main lumen. Secretes glycoproteins associated with mucus.

label.value: dark chief cell of parathyroid gland

value.value: A chief cell that is smaller than light chief cells and has a smaller and darker nucleus and a finely granular cytoplasm with many granules.
An endothelial cell found in capillaries.

label.value: ciliated columnar cell of tracheobronchial tree
Ciliated columnar cell of tracheobronchial tree

value.value: A ciliated columnar cell found in the trachea and bronchus. Vary from low to tall columnar; possesses up to 300 cilia at its surface, interspersed with long irregular microvilli with the cilia varying in length from about 6um in the trachea to about 4um in the terminal bronchioles; driving force of the ciliary current in the bronchial tree.

label.value: clear cell of eccrine sweat gland

value.value: A sweat producing cell of eccrine sweat glands. Pyramidal in shape, with its base resting on the basal lamina or myoepitheliocytes, and its microvillus-covered apical plasma membrane line up the intercellular canaliculi. Cell is not stained by hematoxylin or eosin.

label.value: clear chief cell of parathyroid gland

value.value: A chief cell of parathyroid glands that does not stain with hematoxylin or eosin. This cell is larger, has a larger nucleus and fewer secretory granules than dark chief cells.
A cell found within the dental pulp.
An epithelial cell of the uterus.

Epithelioid macrophage is an activated macrophage that resembles an epithelial cell with finely granular, pale eosinophilic cytoplasm and central, ovoid nucleus (oval or elongate). This cell type is able to merge into one another to form aggregates. The presence of such aggregates may characterize some pathologic conditions, mainly granulomatous inflammation.
A promyelocyte that is considerably smaller, with more condensed chromatin, and nucleoli are no longer conspicuous.
A columnar cell of the cervix uteri.
The dead keratin-filled squamous cell of the stratum corneum. This cell type lacks a nucleus.

A promyelocyte with a nucleus that is indented and contains more marginated heterochromatin compared to its precursor cell (myeloblast); cytoplasm is deeply basophilic and contains numerous mitochondria and meandering cysternae of endoplasmic reticulum; largest of the granulocyte lineages.
A crenated erythrocyte with 30+ crenations, bumps or spurs that are the result of damage due to age or disease.
A cell type that makes up the highly vascular membrane lining the marrow cavity of long bones.

label.value: external epithelial cell of tympanic membrane

value.value: Epithelial cell found on the external side of the tympanic membrane
Epithelial cells derived from general body ectoderm and ectoderm placodes.

label.value: basal external epithelial cell of tympanic membrane

value.value: A cell type found in the basal epithelial layer on the external side of the tympanic membrane. Cell type is flattened with intracellular spaces of variable dimensions.

label.value: superficial external epithelial cell of tympanic membrane

value.value: A cell type found on the superficial layer of the external side of the tympanic membrane. This cell-type lacks a nucleus.

label.value: internal epithelial cell of tympanic membrane

value.value: An extremely flattened cell type found on the inner side of the tympanic membrane. The surface of this cell type carries sparse pleomorphic microvilli that are more common near the junctional zones.
A rod-shpaed cell that forms a single row adjacent to and supporting the inner hair cells.
A rod-shaped cell found in 3 or 4 rows that lie adjacent to and support the outer hair cells.
A supporting cell that is attached to the basement membrane and forms rows that support the hair cells.
An epithelial cell that remains from the disintegration of the epithelial root sheath involved in the development of teeth.
A specialized cell involved in sensory perception of smell.
A border cell is a slender columnar cell on the medial portion of the basilar membrane.
An epithelial cell located on the basal lamina of the olfactory epithelium.

label.value: keratinized cell of the oral mucosa

value.value: A keratinized cell located in the hard palate or gingiva.

A rounded or elliptical epithelial cell, with pale-staining open face nucleus and pale cytoplasm rich in free ribosomes and clusters of centrioles; form a distinct basal zone spaced slightly from the basal surface of the epithelium.
A long, spindle-shaped supporting cells arranged in parallel rows that secretes components of the tectorial membrane and potassium ions into the endolymph.

A cell that is a specialized type of pericyte providing structural support for the capillary loops of kidney. A flat, elongated cell with extensive fine cytoplasmic processes found outside the kidney glomerulus near the macula densa and bound laterally by afferent and efferent arterioles. Being phagocytic, this cell participates in the continuous turnover of the basal lamina by removing its outer portion containing residues of filtration, while the lamina is renewed on its inner surface by the endothelial cells.
A cell within the follicle of an ovary.
